# shadcn/ui over raw HTML

This project uses [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com/) (`components.json`, `@/components/ui`). When building or editing UI in TSX, use the installed shadcn component (or add one) instead of bare HTML elements that shadcn wraps.

## Mappings (examples)

| Prefer                                       | Instead of                                                                                                 |
| -------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `Button` from `@/components/ui/button`       | `<button>` (unless a third-party API truly requires a native button ref with no wrapper—then document why) |
| `Input` from `@/components/ui/input`         | `<input>` for text-like fields                                                                             |
| `Label` from `@/components/ui/label`         | `<label>` paired with form controls                                                                        |
| `Checkbox`, `Select`, `Dialog`, `Tabs`, etc. | Native equivalents once added via CLI                                                                      |

Semantic elements without a shadcn twin stay as-is: `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<article>`, `<form>` (compose inside with shadcn `Input`, `Button`, `Label`, …).

## Adding missing primitives

If the needed component is not in `components/ui/`, add it with the project’s shadcn CLI (see [components](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components)), then import from `@/components/ui/<name>`.

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — one-off styled native control
<button className="rounded-md bg-primary px-4 py-2" onClick={...}>
  Save
</button>

// ✅ GOOD — shared variant + a11y patterns from shadcn
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

<Button type="button" onClick={...}>
  Save
</Button>
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<input className="border rounded px-2" {...props} />;

// ✅ GOOD
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";

<Input {...props} />;
```

Match existing imports and naming; extend `@/components/ui` rather than duplicating styles on raw tags.
